summary: An internal email discussing a document scrub that located several documents associated with Jeffrey Epstein that were not included in the main case file because they were deemed not of evidentiary value. The email lists five attached files, including FD-71 forms from 1996 and 2016, and operational orders from 2019.

events.title: 1996 FD-71 Document Creation
events.description: An FD-71 form from 1996, which predates the record-keeping system, was located during a document scrub.

events.title: 2016 FD-71 Document Creation
events.description: An FD-71 form from 2016 was located during a document scrub.

events.title: 2019 Operational Orders Creation
events.description: Operational orders and an operational order form section from 2019 were located during a document scrub.

keyFacts: A complete document scrub located several documents associated with Jeffrey Epstein that were not included in the main case file.
The excluded documents were deemed 'NOT of evidentiary value'.
The located documents include FD-71 forms from 1996 and 2016, and operational orders from 2019.
The 1996 FD-71 predates the agency's electronic record-keeping system.
The email and its attachments appear to be part of an internal review or audit of case materials.
